<div id="top-content">
  <div class="heading-with-actions top-heading">
    <h1>
      <span translate="no">wxGraphicsMatrix</span> 
      <small class="app-vsn" translate="no">(wx v2.5.4)</small>

    </h1>

<a href="wxGraphicsMatrix.md" title="Copy Markdown (hold Ctrl/Cmd and click it to open as Markdown)" class="copy-markdown icon-action" rel="help">
  <i class="ri-markdown-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  <span class="sr-only">Copy Markdown</span>
</a>



      <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxGraphicsMatrix.erl#L58" title="View Source" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow">
        <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        <span class="sr-only">View Source</span>
      </a>

  </div>


    <section id="moduledoc">
<p>A <a href="wxGraphicsMatrix.html"><code class="inline">wxGraphicsMatrix</code></a> is a native representation of an affine matrix.</p><p>The contents are specific and private to the respective renderer. Instances are ref
counted and can therefore be assigned as usual. The only way to get a valid instance is
via <a href="wxGraphicsContext.html#createMatrix/2"><code class="inline">wxGraphicsContext:createMatrix/2</code></a> or <a href="wxGraphicsRenderer.html#createMatrix/2"><code class="inline">wxGraphicsRenderer:createMatrix/2</code></a>.</p><p>This class is derived, and can use functions, from:</p><ul><li><a href="wxGraphicsObject.html"><code class="inline">wxGraphicsObject</code></a></li></ul><p>wxWidgets docs: <a rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.wxwidgets.org/3.2/classwx_graphics_matrix.html">wxGraphicsMatrix</a></p>
    </section>

</div>

